values:
Started at 9 pm.

Ended at 1:13 am.

All I can say is...

EITO RANNNGGGGEERRRRRR

They are baaaaaaaaaaaaaaaccccccccccccckkkkkkkkkkkkkkkkkk...

Now it`s time to go to my hotel room, eat ice cream, and pass out until it`s time for me to drag my sorry self to Shin-Osaka station to catch my shinkansen back to Yokohama.

Setlist: [Opening VTR] 1. LIFE ~Me no mae no mukou e~ 2. Uchuu ni Itta Lion 3. Rolling Coaster 4. Tsubusa ni Koi [MC] 5. Monjai Beat 6. It's my soul 7. T.W.L 8. Kagayakeru Butai e 9. Scarecrow (Ryo solo) 10. Pan panda (Yoko and Maru) 11. Water Drop 12. Fight for the Eight 13. 365nichi Kazoku 14. I to U 15. EIGHTOPOP!!!!!!! 16. Fly High [MC] 17. Dye D? 18. wander 19. Kyuu Jou Show!! 20. Zukkoke Otokomichi 21. Wonderful World!! 22. Yona Yona Yo Night (Shota, Hina, and Ohkura) 23. A (Subaru solo) [Band session] 24. Misetekure 25. Do you agree? 26. Hi & high [Final words -- Subaru] 27. My Home [Encore I] 28. Mugendai 29. Musekinin Hero 30. Freedom Riron [Encore II] 31. Monjai Beat ------------------------------- Show started at 6:00 and ended at 9:15. I'm not typing up a full report yet but my thoughts/highlights: -the opening VTR (it was more like a movie) was a lot of fun. Shota kissed a girl, Yoko kissing giving CPR to Hina (who died twice), Ohkura and Maru as bikers, Hina coming back to life one time by having money waving in front of his nose (lol), and then it all coming together as them going out to the field to play baseball... -I forget but it was either one or two voices that introduced them after the VTR ended; they were coming out to play a match (in other words, the concert) and each member was introduced one after one with their numbers. -They played the full band for the first few songs. There was also a brass section and strings section on the stage. -For the opening greetings, it was really really short. Hina said his usual stuff and I think Yoko was the other only other member who even talked. -they got in the big moving carts during Monjai Beat (which were decorated all Christmas-y with candy canes and stuff) -T.W.L was on the backstage, I like the butt shaking -Ryo played acoustic guitar and sung Scarecrow on the center stage. The VTR on the screen showed an old guy making/building something? I wonder if Japanese people even know what a scarecrow is...the lyrics work but the VTR didn't. -Pan panda was sooo cute. I think this may have been the best performance, lol. Yoko and Maru wore panda costumes (I TOTALLY saw that coming!) and there were other backdancers dressed up as animals (I was having flashbacks to Maru's solo at their 2009-2010 Countdown concert in Osaka). I think Yoko lip-synched his parts (Maru was singing live though). During the song, a bunch of balloons floated around (most were above the arena seats but there at least 2 that made it over first floor stand seats) and they dropped paper and little pandas onto the audience. -Water Drop was totally ripped off a KAT-TUN performance. Seriously, I had a friend who used to love them so I was forced to see them more than once and I swear, it was the same thing with all the water coming out of the stage and stuff. -Fight for the Eight was cool because their costumes glowed in the dark and when the lights were dimmed, you could just see their lighted silhouttes. Okay, that was a bad description but it was cool. -I don't really remember was they talked about during the MC but it was mostly about their families (mostly their little brothers and their girlfriends, lol). Then someone (Subaru? I forget) that they should sing 365 again. There was also a huge commotion when Yoko called Ryo Nishikido-kun (instead of Dokkun) when talking about their work. Everyone started yelling at Yoko to apologize and then Maru (? I forget) made Yoko say the 3 things he liked about Ryo best while apologizing. So Yoko said he liked that Ryo always works hard, his coolness and his moles (XD). "Which ones?" (he has two on his face) "BOTH!" lol -there was a really cool VTR/music video that went with Dye D? (totally called the haunted house thing!). I think I just watched the music video instead of watching them perform on the stage, lol -I didn't really get what they were trying to do during Yona Yona; they were wearing wings on their costumes and well, it didn't make much sense (not that the song makes much sense anyway). -Subaru gave a really nice message before singing A (about being able to say thank you; it's simple but hard to convey). The audience sang along for the "arigatou" parts -- that went on for awhile, at one point, everyone thought the sing a long was over so everyone stopped but then Subaru's like, "wait, don't stop!" lol -Shota started off the band session on his electric guitar on the center stage. Ryo, Maru, and Ohkura all joined in. It was really really short. -hearing Do you agree? again was nice. <3 -My home was a nice way to end the concert, plus they played it live. <333 -I was so surprised to hear Mugendai for the encore; I was so worried they dropped the song. It was nice to get some more sing a long this year. -Apparently the Sapporo show ended with Hitotsu no Uta but instead they did Monjai Beat again (I wonder if they'll do Hitotsu no Uta for the last Tokyo Dome show and in Osaka?) Overall: it was fun and it was nice to see them again but there was no game/skit, so it felt like something was really missing. I think they wayyyy overdid the lights and special effects (umm, what was this about saving energy again? Even though Tokyo Denryoku lifted the energy saving ban in September, I think this was way overdoing it). The old songs were really the most fun. What the hell happened to Yellow Pansy Street???? I love that song and would've rathered that over LIFE. It sort of felt like any other JE concert to be honest. Usually they have a skit/game to make it very Eito but this felt like any other group could've done. I still have three more shows to go (Tokyo on Sunday night, Osaka on the 30th and Countdown on the night of the 31st) so we'll see if my opinion changes.
